titlestmt.titleproper: A Guide to the Rockefeller Foundation records, Biographical File FA485

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on 2015-09-19 00:24:32 -0400.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The Rockefeller Foundation Biographical File is arranged alphabetically by the last name/family name of the individual or by institutional name.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Collection is open for scholarly research.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Information regarding the Rockefeller Archive Center's preferred elements and forms of citation can be found at http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Level 2 Limited Processing has been conducted by RAC to establish basic intellectual and physical control of the material and assess immediate preservation and conservation needs. Records have been rehoused into acid-free boxes. All records remain in original folders.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: The Rockefeller Foundation Biographical File was created and maintained by the Foundation staff until the 1980's, at which time the File was transferred to the Rockefeller Archive Center.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The scope and breadth of the Biographical File is inconsistent. Some files are rich, while others are sparse.

Individual files may contain: biographical sketches, curriculum vitaes and resumes, obituaries, press releases, photographs, articles and publications. Files may also document honors, awards, appointments and positions held.
